{
  "texts": [
    "That is, write:",
    "for some s > 0.",
    "The first term is bounded by s, so we can use exponential moments inequalities on it, while I used inequalities on the tails P(|ℓ i (θ)| ≥ s) to control the second term.",
    "For the sake of completeness I state one of the bounds obtained by this technique (with s = n/λ).",
    "Theorem 5.2 (Corollary 2.5, Alquier (2006))."
  ]
}